    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(SN) Die dominico qui est pridie nonae februarii. In presencia <rs
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonorum hominum</rs> [q]uorum nomina hic
                        subter leguntur: <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>
                        <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Count" ref="#people/4027">[R]ambaldus</persName>,
                            <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name
                                ref="Iohannes/Bonus/ de Guastalla">Iohannes Bonus</name></persName>
                        de <placeName ref="#places/33">Varstalla</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name ref="Amvbrosius/ de Claveca"
                                >[Am]brosius</name></persName> de Claveca, <persName
                            ref="#people/3594" key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #siblingOf #childOf"
                            >Bonefacius</persName> [et] <persName ref="#people/3595"
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #siblingOf #childOf"
                            >[Ga]rsedonius</persName>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">germanis</rs>
                        <rs key="#childOf">filiis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count #Marquis/duke #parentOf" ref="#people/3571"
                            >Alberti</persName> comes et <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs> et
                            <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name ref="Benzo/de Carpeneta"
                                >Benzo</name></persName> de <placeName>Carpeneta</placeName>,
                            <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines"><name
                                ref="Gherardus/de Richindonna">Girardus</name></persName> de
                        Richindonna et re[li]qui plures. Ibique in eorum presencia [Alber]tus comes
                        et marchio investivit do[min]um <persName><name ref="Richardus"
                                >Richardum</name></persName> et <persName key="#Missus"
                            ref="#people/3574">Albertum Campanile</persName>, <rs key="#Missus"
                            >mi[s]so</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Missus" ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancii
                            Benedicti Lariane</orgName>, de toto <rs>pignore</rs> quod habuit
                            <persName ref="#people/3707">Ugezone</persName> de
                            <placeName>Panzano</placeName> ab eodem marchione Alberto [in] [lo]co
                            <placeName key="#Castle #Cereals #Legumes #Forests #Wine #Houses"
                            ref="#places/34">Pigongaga</placeName> sive in <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castro</rs> sive ex[tra] cast[r]urn sive in <rs key="#Cereals #Legumes"
                            >campis</rs> sive in <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs> sive [in <rs
                            key="#Wine">v]ineis</rs> sive in <rs key="#Houses">casis</rs> sive in
                        omnibus locis [a]d ipsum pignus pertinentibus, quantum ad predictum
                        marchionem Albertum exinde pertinet, predicto monasterio in perpe[t]uum sine
                        sua et heredum suorum contra[dict]ione pro anima sua dedit. Factum est
                        [a]nno ab incarnatione domini nostri Iesu Christi millesimo centesimo
                        centesimo XXXIIII, indictione XII. Actum in castro <placeName key="#Castle"
                            ref="#places/259">Runco</placeName>. Feliciter. (SN) Ego <persName
                            key="#Notary #Witness"><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ro[gat]us ibi interfuit et <rs
                            key="#Witness">subscirsit</rs> [et com]plevi. </ab>
                </div>
